textBeforeTable: General Examinations CLEP Examination Evaluations Ithaca College, at the discretion of the student's dean or program director, accepts credit from the College Level Examination Program (CLEP). Credit is awarded for both general and subject examinations as outlined in the chart below. Test results should be sent directly to the Office of the Registrar. A limited number of CLEP credits may be applied toward general education requirements; see "Advanced Placement Policy." For additional information about Ithaca College's CLEP policy, please contact Charlotte Richardson in the Office of the Registrar, 220 Job Hall, 607-274-1210.
